description.0: The Nimrod Sentinel takes on the Juggernaut! Can the X-Men stop the fight before the collateral damage becomes too great? Meanwhile, Storm finds trouble back in her native Kenya.
description.3: Moondragon embraces the evil of the Dragon of the Moon! Can the Defenders bring her back to the light, or will she continue down her villainous path?
description.6: Silver Sable's first appearance! The bounty-hunter organization Silver Sable Inc. always gets their man...dead or alive! They've set their sights on the crook called Fox, and Spidey must do everything he can to save him!
description.7: The Olympian Apollo visits Avengers Mansion to gift Hercules with new battle garb. During a team meeting, Wasp is reinstated as chairwoman and Black Knight accepts a bid! Allegiances will shift, as the Avengers find their footing under new leadership.
description.8: Captain America and Captain Britain wage war against the Dark Mage Modred! But the question is will they survive?
description.9: Captain Britain takes on the Technet while his sister battles his counterpart.
description.10: There's a new Dark Lord in the galaxy, and she's out for Luke's head! Not only must Luke fight Lumiya, he must also deal with who and, more dangerously, what she really is!
description.15: Conan simply desires a good night's sleep at an inn, but with bandits lurking in the shadows, Conan will not get his wish!
description.16: Joey and Top Dog are the best of friends, but when Top Dog is caught as an international spy we'll find out if this is a case of espionage or mistaken identity!
description.19: Jim Shooter spills SECRET WARS secrets!
description.20: Reflecting on the past, the Gargoyle, once called Isaac Christians, decides to return home only to find the impossible!
description.24: The Fantastic Four just wouldn't be the same without the Thing (beyond basic arithmetic). Ben Grimm decides to call it quits on Marvel's First Family. But why?
description.26: The struggle for control continues between Moondragon and Dragon of the Moon! Who will win this internal tug-of-war?
description.29: A look at Epic Comics’ STARSTRUCK!
description.30: Captain Britain does battle with his evil other-dimensional doppelganger, Kaptain Briton!
description.31: There's a new Dark Lord in the galaxy, and she's out for Luke's head! Not only must Luke fight Lumiya, he must also deal with who and, more dangerously, what she really is!
description.32: Every day Daredevil brawls with criminals on the streets of New York City, but in this issue, he uses a new weapon against crime... The Performing Arts!
description.33: Can Hulk save his Puffball friend...and the dimension they've been dragged to?
description.34: It starts as a simple headache. But it's one that just won't stop! Rhodey realizes he must get help for his mysterious malady from disgraced Avenger Henry Pym. Meanwhile, the West Coast Avengers are desperately trying to find the original Iron Man who is lost at sea!
description.35: The madness of David Haller! Stunning revelations unfold as the true parentage and mental secrets of Legion are revealed!
description.37: It's the Doctor Doom revival no one saw coming! Doom is back with a vengeance- in the body of his young apprentice Kristoff Vernard!
description.38: Thunderbird has kidnapped Banshee and sent a message to the X-Men: if they do not find their former teammate within 24 hours, Thunderbird will kill him!
description.40: Spider-Man helps nursing home resident Pops Magee stay in his home. Plus, Red 9! Is he the latest teenage super hero- or villain?
description.41: Wasp is shocked to discover the Vision's deterred "world domination" plans. The Vision, accompanied by Scarlet Witch, goes to to a debriefing in D.C. that will save public image. Plus, Captain Marvel finds herself in hot water after a failed rescue mission.
description.42: Captain America is no stranger to weird visions or memories from his past! But when his visions lead him to England, what will the Star-Spangled Avenger find? Enter: Captain Britain!
description.47: Her name is Zarmi! Her quest is to create a new empire, with her as its queen, and it looks like she's going to succeed! But only one man refuses to fall under her hypnotic spell; Conan. Yet what can even Hyborea's greatest barbarian do against Zarmi's ever-growing legions?
description.51: While Ben Grimm battles Grimm the Sorcerer, Ultron mobilizes his new army!
description.56: When all of New York is threatened with blindness, Daredevil must save the day. How does The Cossack hope to pull off his latest crime spree? Plus, Glori O'Breen may be telling half-truths, and Black Widow re-emerges in DD's life.
description.57: Hulk refuses to join the crew of energy-eaters Klaatu, Captain Cybor and Xeron. But is Hulk's immense strength enough to ward off these diabolical menaces?
description.58: Rhodey makes the difficult decision to resign from the West Coast Avengers. Meanwhile, the West Coast Avengers learn that Tony Stark was the original Iron Man!
description.59: Moira Mactaggert's newest patient, David Haller, is on a rampage! Will the New Mutants be able to stop this powerful new threat?
description.60: The final confrontation between Spider-Man and his new costume!
description.61: Doctor Strange guest-stars! The Sorcerer Supreme helps Reed, Susan and Franklin Richards with their latest mystical debacle- Mephisto!
description.62: Warlock's father Magus has come to Earth to kill him, but not if Nightcrawler, Colossus, and Rogue can help it!
description.64: At Fontane College, the Beast is faced with the responsibility of being an advocate for mutant rights!
description.66: This one's really different! A kid worships super-villains and at long last he attains his heart's desire, the chance to impersonate Spider-Man! See what that does to Spidey's less than reputable reputation,and more, in "The Spectacular Spider-Kid!"
description.67: The fight to save the world begins, as the Avengers take on their own teammate! Who will win? Who will lose? Who will perish? Don't miss the Avenger most exciting showdown yet!
description.68: Stane International has Cap's mighty shield! And Cap has vowed to get it back! But can even the legendary skill of the star-spangled Avenger overcome an opponent who wears armor created from the same mysterious metal as Cap's invincible shield?
description.69: VASTAR THE VILE descends on the Royal Castle with a giant metal locust in tow.
description.71: A young girl with a mysterious power draws Storm, Wasp, Tigra and She-Hulk to her small town to stop the menance of A.I.M!
description.73: A shaman hired Conan to help him find his tribe's stolen idol. But that search soon becomes a deadly fight for freedom against the merciless female bounty hunters known as the Iron Damsels!
description.76: Creator Bill Mantlo talks Rocket Racoon! And a CLOAK AND DAGGER special look with pages from Ed Hannigan.
description.77: Sidney Crumb is turning into a horrific monster -- but why? And how will Captain Britain contend with this strange threat?
description.78: Han, Luke, Leia, Chewie, Lando, C3PO and R2-D2 are up to their ears in Ewoks and trouble when war breaks out between the Ewoks and Lahsbees!
description.83: Within his phony Baxter Building, Grimm the Sorcerer tells his prisoner Tarianna about his plans to eliminate Ben Grimm!
description.89: The Gael does something desperate to escape prison. Is Glorianna O 'Breen in trouble once again? And, who is the Old Woman of Beare? The IRA rises!
description.90: Hulk attacks the U-Foes with some surprising assistance. Meanwhile, what will the Senate say when Doc Strange informs them of Ol' Greenskin's whereabouts?
description.91: It's Iron Man vs. Iron Man in the cruelest battle of all. It's friend against friend in the struggle for final custody of Iron Man's armor! Will Tony Stark beat Rhodey? Or will the ever-deadly Vibro kill them both, instead?
description.93: Can Reed and Sue protect their new home before a demonic prophecy is fulfilled...on their front lawn?
description.94: Even if the X-Men defeat Kulan Gath (and the hidden-right-in-front-of-them Selene), will they be able to restore Manhattan to its former state?
description.95: With the mutated plant creatures inching closer to infecting the world, will the Defenders be able to uproot this ever-growing problem?

2.text: The villainous Rhino is possessed by the mind-bending Miracle Man! Ben Grimm was trying to catch a break, but that’s not happening this issue!

5.text: The kids learn the value of teamwork when they are confronted by sewer alligators while trying to save a kitten.

12.text: Marc Spector, AKA Moon Knight, establishes the Spector International Art Gallery to sell off his most prized possession—a statue of Khonshu. Will Spector abandon the Moon Knight persona for good?

13.text: Iceman enters his final battle with Oblivion -- and should the X-Man fail against his monstrous might, Hell itself might freeze over!

16.text: Top Dog is a foreign spy? Or has there been a case of mutt mix-up!?

17.text: Viking raids, unicorns and magic! Wally the Wizard runs into adventure head first!

18.text: The Beauty and the Beast take their final stand in the arena! But where does Doctor Doom factor into the equation? Plus, will the bonds of romance remain once the chains of bondage have been broken?

19.text: Jim Shooter spills SECRET WARS secrets!

21.text: Thor awakens in a strange place while Beta Ray Bill, Sif, and the Warriors Three travel the Earth. Meanwhile, Loki enlists the help of Lorelei in his quest for the throne!

22.text: Aurora and Northstar head to the circus to seek an old friend, who may be able to help Aurora deal with her split personality! But what they find is far from entertaining - the circus has been overtaken by the domineering Pink Pearl!

23.text: Rocket Raccoon must prevent total intergalactic war.

24.text: The Fantastic Four just wouldn't be the same without the Thing (beyond basic arithmetic). Ben Grimm decides to call it quits on Marvel's First Family. But why?

27.text: A call from a friend from high school leads Alison to a mystery where all is not as it seems!

28.text: Danny is dying, and none of the world's scientists can help! Iron Fist must return to K'un-Lun, the fabled land of his teachers. But can even Power Man get him there in time?

29.text: A look at Epic Comics’ STARSTRUCK!

44.text: The kids, along with Friday and Marrina, go after Snake-Eyes where they corner him in a sunken ship!

45.text: Kneesaa steps on a Nightshade thorn and Wicket Wystri Warrick & Teebo must find the cure, the nectar of the Sunnydew flower, which is in the possession of Gantu.

48.text: Spider-Ham visits the mysterious island of Ducktor Doom. But why has the Fantastic Fur driven him off to his own island?

49.text: Mystery abounds in Cashelot as the royal crown goes missing! Can Royal Roy and Gummy find it before the coronation ceremony?

50.text: Will Wally win the Magic-athon?! And without a magic trick to his name?

51.text: While Ben Grimm battles Grimm the Sorcerer, Ultron mobilizes his new army!

52.text: Master of the Mystic Arts Doctor Strange takes on Tymon! One of Doc's strangest villains yet!

53.text: NOTHING TO FEAR The heroes have defeated their enemies--all save one. Now, with the stolen power of The Beyonder himself, Doctor Doom strikes! Who can stop him now?

54.text: As Hela makes her move for Odin's body, Thor must find a way to bring the Asgardians back home. But how can he with the Rainbow Bridge gone?

55.text: Alpha Flight vs. alchemy! Gilded Lily is revealed to be a disciple of the dread Diablo, and her mystical powers are more than a match for Aurora and Sasquatch!

65.text: Kitty must choose Ogun's fate. Will she allow him to live or condemn him to death?

69.text: VASTAR THE VILE descends on the Royal Castle with a giant metal locust in tow.

70.text: Trapped in a spatial void, Iceman is greeted by past teammates to help him with present woes! The X-Men, Champions and Defenders guest-star!

74.text: Top Dog is dognapped! Who will come to the canine's rescue?

75.text: Power Man is trapped inside an arctic bunker! Iron Fist is stranded outside it! While Luke is starving to death, Danny is freezing to death! And there's no rescue in sight!

76.text: Creator Bill Mantlo talks Rocket Racoon! And a CLOAK AND DAGGER special look with pages from Ed Hannigan.

79.text: It’s show time and the stakes are terrifying! Despite Beast’s disapproval, Dazzler continues her new gig at a mutant gladiatorial arena. But just as Hank discovers the dangerous serum that is spiking Dazzler’s powers out of control, he too is injected – and turns entirely feral!

82.text: The hypnotic Snake-Eyes crash lands at the aquarium that Power Pack is visiting!

83.text: Within his phony Baxter Building, Grimm the Sorcerer tells his prisoner Tarianna about his plans to eliminate Ben Grimm!

84.text: Featuring three can’t-miss Cloak & Dagger tales! What happens when Dagger dances at a discotheque? Find out here!

85.text: ...AND DUST TO DUST The penultimate chapter of SECRET WARS is here! The face of Doom is revealed!

86.text: Thor and Odin have been defeated! Now Surtur is free to enact his devious plan. But is there no one left to stand against him? What of Loki? Can the God of Mischief put aside his tricks to save his kingdom?

87.text: Aurora and Sasquatch discover their potential new Alpha Flight base has an unexpected tenant - the mysterious Gilded Lily! Are her good intentions genuine, or just plated? Plus - is Elizabeth destined (or doomed) to be Talisman forever?

88.text: It all converges here! Spider's symbiote suit is on the loose, and all of New York is threatened. Spider-Man and Black Cat find themselves in heated battle with the Kingpin and his strange lackey, Spot! Peter Parker is plagued with nightmares that may foretell a dark future.

96.text: Alison gets a new job as a singer at the Ace of Clubs Club but she may have to do more fighting than singing for the club to stay in business.

98.text: Power Pack forges a friendship with Cloak and Dagger!

99.text: Luke and Danny take a field test to prove their mettle to a potential client. But the test is a killer... literally!
